<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Useful general education skills</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Here are a few general education skills practical for the workplace:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Problem-solving skills</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Critical thinking and problem-solving skills allow students to develop and use investigative methods to come up with new solutions, while also analyzing existing solutions. General education classes encourage students to identify problems and develop their own solutions. This skill can be beneficial in many industries, including business, healthcare, research or medical, where it can help employees come up with creative solutions to problems in the workplace.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Related:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/resumes-cover-letters/problem-solving-skills" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><strong>Problem-Solving Skills: Definitions and Examples</strong></a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Teamwork</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Teamwork is the collective efforts of a group of people, all working toward one goal. Many general education class requirements have students work together to research and complete a project, teaching them valuable teamwork skills. Teamwork is an important skill in most careers, including healthcare, business, education or sales, where employees must work and collaborate with others to help customers, clients or patients.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Related:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/career-development/teamwork-and-collaboration" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><strong>Teamwork and Collaboration: What They Are and How To Improve Them</strong></a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
